<rubyforge xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Contribute</title>

  <page>
    <xi:include href="../_menu.xml" />

    <content>
      <section label="contribute" title="Contribute">
        <subsection label="style" title="Coding Style">
          <p>
            Inorder to keep the source-code of <project-title /> clean
            and readable, those who wish to contribute code to
            <project-title /> should review the project's
            <a href="style.html">coding style guide-lines</a>.
          </p>
        </subsection>

        <subsection label="github" title="Git and GitHub">
          <p>
            Since Ronin makes extensive use of
            <a href="http://www.git-scm.org/">Git</a> and
            <a href="http://github.com/">GitHub</a>, having a
            <a href="https://github.com/login">github.com</a> account and
            understanding Git workflow is crucial to contributors. Not to
            worry, we have a good overview of
            <a href="git_and_github.html">Git and GitHub</a>.
          </p>
        </subsection>

        <subsection label="dive" title="Dive In">
          <p>
            Once your familiar with Ronin's coding style,
            and setup with <a href="http://www.git-scm.com/">Git</a>
            and <a href="http://www.github.com/">GitHub</a>,
            you can dive right into Ronin. Just pick a repository,
            fork it and dive in:
          </p>

          <list>
            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin">Ronin</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-dorks">Ronin Dorks</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-exploits">Ronin Exploits</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-gen">Ronin Gen</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-html">Ronin HTML</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-php">Ronin PHP</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-scanners">Ronin Scanners</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-sql">Ronin SQL</a>
            </item>

            <item>
              <a href="http://github.com/postmodern/ronin-web">Ronin Web</a>
            </item>
          </list>
        </subsection>
      </section>
    </content>
  </page>
